        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-11-16 14:52:24.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\nAfter reading up on \"draft\" changes in Gerrit, I believe someone submitted this change using git review with the -D argument, which made it into a draft.\n\nAccording to this article https://nofluffjuststuff.com/magazine/2016/04/understanding_and_applying_gerrit_part_3_gerrit_submit_types_and_git_review , if the owner of the draft clicks on the change (which should appear in their My -> Drafts tab), they should see the option to delete the change, as can be seen in this screenshot: https://nofluffjuststuff.com/s/magazine/2016/04/271_images/gerrit-draft-change.jpg\n\nWho was the original submitter of this draft change, and can they see the option to delete it?",
        "patchset_number": 1
